track.name: Helena
comments: we'll meet again, when both our cars COLLIDE

One of some really good stuff from crappy band. Decent riffs, melodies, overall idea, lyrics and interesting backing  vocals, reminds of choruses in Greek tragedies. Even one more hint to song title. Catchy song. Sadly, the band decided to get into MTV-trash style.

The vocalist can do really good job, if he WAS allowed to, reminds me of Bruce Dickinson at some points.
So long and not good night
This brings back sooo many memories. I haven't heard this tune in forever YES
I think it's the best song to watch the asteroids smash into the Earth to. [4]
The first song I heard by them, back in 2006 and IMO, their best so far.
This song marked a time of my life. Fuckin' amazing!
